An Act
ENROLLED HOUSE
BILL NO. 3764 By: Turner and Wolfley of the
House
and
Hamilton and Burns of the
Senate
An Act relating to gang-related offenses; amending 21
O.S. 2021, Section 856.3, as last amended by Section
25 of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1627 of the 2nd
Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, which
relates to condition of membership; criminalizing
certain acts related to foreign terrorist
organizations; providing for penalties; authorizing a
court to take judicial notice of certain designation;
updating statutory language; and providing an
effective date.
SUBJECT: Gang-related offenses
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 856.3, as
last amended by Section 25 of Enrolled Senate Bill No. 1627 of the
2nd Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, is amended to read as
follows:
Section 856.3. A. Any person who attempts or commits a gang-
related offense as a condition of membership in a criminal street
gang or while in association with any criminal street gang or gang
member shall be guilty of a Class B5 felony offense punishable upon
conviction by imprisonment in the custody of the Department of
Corrections for a term of five (5) years, which shall be in addition
to any other penalty imposed. For purposes of this section
subsection, “criminal street gang” is defined by subsection F of
Section 856 of this title and “gang-related offense” means those
offenses enumerated in subsection F of Section 856 of this title.

B. Any person who attempts or commits a gang-related offense as
a condition of membership of, while in association with, acting on
behalf of, or knowingly supporting any foreign terrorist
organization shall be guilty of a Class B5 felony offense punishable
upon conviction by imprisonment in the custody of the Department of
Corrections for a term of five (5) years, which shall be in addition
to any other penalty imposed. For purposes of this subsection,
“foreign terrorist organization” means any organization designated
by the United States Department of State as such pursuant to 8
U.S.C., Section 1189. The court may take judicial notice of such
designation as published in the Federal Register or maintained by
the United States Department of State.
SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
